<TITLE> Saifur Rahman's death a loss to the nation: Muhith </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 5 (bdnews24.com)Finance minister A M A Muhith described the sudden death of veteran BNP leader M Saifur Rahman in a car crash on Saturday as "a loss to the nation". "Saifur Rahman was my friend and Sylhet has lost a son to be proud of," Muhith told bdnews24.com, shortly after Rahman's death. The 77-year-old Rahman, Bangladesh's longest serving finance minister, succumbed to fatal injuries at around 3pm after his car lost control on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway. "The nation will long remember his contribution to the economy of the country," said Muhith. He said Bangladesh had lost a true patriot in Rahman, and extended his sympathies to the family. b
